# README.md
readme.md file is a overview of all files in the project including title, author, topic, copyright information, etc. should also indicate how the project is organized & instructions on how to reproduce the project 
```{r}
sessionInfo()
```

# naming conventions

- Scripts: 00_File-name
- R objects: using underscore (e.g. health_data)
comments written with ##
- functions labeled with BigCamelCase
- filanames using _ if with numbers then - or just - 


# data structure

/data
/source
/docs with child .Rmd 
/output with /figures 
/temp
/
Makefile
README.md

# comments

all source code files begin with comment header including: 
    - a description of what the file does
    - the date it was last updated
    - the name of the file's creator and any contributors

# creating final product

- Use child .Rmd documents in final doc
- will need to load original CSV file to the final HTML (or each child directory) then source relevant code to analyze 
- use this site for figure settings: http://zevross.com/blog/2017/06/19/tips-and-tricks-for-working-with-images-and-figures-in-r-markdown-documents/
- if you don't want error messages or warnings, set warning, message and error to F



# Misc

- load relevant packages at the beginning of each doc
- see p. 116 of reproducible research in R for example GNU make
